Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal (P, T, x, y) data have been measured for the binary system carbon dioxide + 2-propanol at temperatures from (293 to 323) K. The pressure range under investigation was between (0.68 and 8.6) MPa. The new experimental data are correlated with the Soave-Redlich-Kwong (SRK) equation of state coupled with the HVID mixing rules. A correlation of the HVID parameters with temperature is proposed by using all reliable published data and those of this study.
Citation.sTitle: High-Pressure Vapor-Liquid Equilibria in the System Carbon Dioxide and 2-Propanol at Temperatures from 293.25 K to 323.15 K
